      "message": "[critical] Line 87: 🔴 **Breaking change: missing default value for `shutdownConnections`**\n\nThe underlying C++ API in `configurationmanager_interface.h` (line 48) declares this parameter with a default:\n```\nvoid setAccountActive(const std::string\u0026 accountId, bool active, bool shutdownConnections \u003d false);\n```\n\nHowever, the SWIG interface here omits the default value. This means all existing Java/Android callers of `setAccountActive(accountId, active)` will fail to compile — the two-argument overload no longer exists in the generated JNI bindings. This is a source-breaking change for downstream consumers.\n\nSWIG supports default argument values and will generate overloaded methods for them.\n\n```suggestion\nvoid setAccountActive(const std::string\u0026 accountId, bool active, bool shutdownConnections \u003d false);\n```",
